cs.NE, cs.CE, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.LG

The paper discusses the use of genetic algorithms for global optimization, which falls under the category of evolutionary computation. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses benchmark functions, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of genetic algorithms for optimization also falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
